heir ability to keep up with rising costs of urban life. Scholars and policy and planning professionals alike will benefit from Shatkin's comprehensive research. Cities for Profit contains insights from more than 150 interviews, site visits to projects, and data from government and nongovernmental organization reports and data, urban plans, architectural renderings, annual reports and promotional materials of developers, and newspaper and other media accounts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity planningzAsia. 0aLand use, UrbanxGovernment policyzAsia. 0aReal estate developmentxGovernment policyzAsia. 0aReal estate investmentxGovernment policyzAsia. 0aUrban policyzAsia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aUrban Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501709715zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501709715.jpg  a978-3-11-063851-6  Urban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019c2016d2019  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  a